d 'XTHPOOL': module to perform Hausman poolability test for cointegrated panels (Westerlund and Hess 2011) 
d
d      xthpool implements the poolability test of Westerlund and
d Hess (2011, Journal of Applied Econometrics). Consider the   
d cointegrated panel	    y_it = a_i + b_i x_it + e_it,    where
d b_i is a unit-specific slope vector and the error e_it may
d contain r common factors, so the cross-sectional units are   
d dependent. The test evaluates the null hypothesis of poolability 
d	H0: b_i = b for all i	 against the heterogeneous
d alternative that at least one unit differs. It compares an
d individual and a pooled bias-adjusted    least-squares estimator
d of the cointegrating slope, unit by unit, in a Hausman (1978)
d way, and takes the maximum of the    individual Hausman
d statistics. After a Gumbel normalization the statistic has a
d well-defined limiting distribution even when N    is of the same
d order as T — a regime where the seemingly-unrelated Wald test
d of Mark, Ogaki and Sul (2005) is badly distorted. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: structural breaks
d KW:  cointegration
d KW: Hausman
d KW: poolability
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260711
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xthpool.ado
f xthpool.sthlp
f xthpool_methods.sthlp
f xthpool_example.do
